# Task Manager API

A secure RESTful API for managing personal tasks. 
- `node-api/` — Node.js + Express.js


Uses **PostgreSQL** for user storage and **MongoDB** for task storage.

---

## Folder Structure

```
task-manager/
├── node-api/                   # Node.js version
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── config/             # DB connection setup (postgres.js, mongo.js)
│   │   ├── controllers/        # Business logic (user.controller.js, task.controller.js)
│   │   ├── middleware/         # JWT auth + global error handler
│   │   ├── models/             # Mongoose task schema
│   │   ├── routes/             # Route definitions (auth, tasks)
│   │   └── validators/         # Joi validation schemas
│   ├── server.js               # Entry point
│   ├── .env.example
│   ├── docker-compose.yml
│   └── package.json


### So my Design Decisions

- **PostgreSQL for users** — User data is relational (unique emails, auth), so a SQL database is the right fit.
- **MongoDB for tasks** — Tasks have optional/flexible fields and belong to one user, making a document store clean and simple.
- **JWT stateless auth** — No session storage needed; each request carries its own identity.
- **Joi / Pydantic** — Validation is kept in a dedicated layer, separate from business logic.
- **Controllers/Services split** — Route files only define paths; all logic lives in controllers.

